text: USS Oneida has been the name of more than one United States Navy ship, and may refer to: * , a brig commissioned in 1810, sold in 1815, repurchased, and sold again in 1825 * , a screw sloop of war in commission from 1862 to 1865 and from 1867 until wrecked in 1870 * , a patrol vessel in commission from April to September 1898 and during September 1912 and in commission as USS Henry P. Williams (SP-509) and USS SP-509 in 1918–1919 * , the proposed name and designation of a yacht considered for use as a patrol vessel during World War I but never acquired by the Navy * , a patrol vessel in commission from 1918 to 1919 * , an attack transport in commission from 1944 to 1946 Category:United States Navy ship names
title: USS Oneida
